author: Herald Staff
title: Herald Heroes
text:
OFFENSE — Dalyn Williams, QB, Dartmouth. Senior was 29-of-53 for school-record 435 yards and four TDs in a 35-3 drubbing of Yale. Williams (7,525 yards) also broke Big Green career mark for total offense held by former NFL quarterback Jay Fiedler, who was on hand to witness feat.
DEFENSE — Sam McDonald, S, Bentley. Junior from Norfolk had a pair of interceptions, the second one coming with 16 seconds to play to cement a 19-14 win against Saint Anselm.
SPECIAL TEAMS — Grant Senne, K, Brown. Senior booted three field goals, including a 35-yard winner in the final minutes, in 25-24 victory at Holy Cross.
